data.value: Creates a DataFrame object from a structured ndarray, sequence of tuples or dicts, or DataFrame.

children.type_: structured ndarray, sequence of tuples or dicts, or DataFrame

data.value: Field of array to use as the index, alternately a specific set of input labels to use.

Column names to use. If the passed data do not have names associated with them, this argument provides names for the columns. Otherwise this argument indicates the order of the columns in the result (any names not found in the data will become all-NA columns).
Attempt to convert values of non-string, non-numeric objects (like decimal.Decimal) to floating point, useful for SQL result sets.
Number of rows to read if data is an iterator.
Convert structured or record ndarray to DataFrame.
Data can be provided as a structured ndarray:

data.out:
col_1 col_2
0      3     a
1      2     b
2      1     c
3      0     d

data.value: Data can be provided as a list of dicts:

data.out:
col_1 col_2
0      3     a
1      2     b
2      1     c
3      0     d

data.value: Data can be provided as a list of tuples with corresponding columns:

data.out:
col_1 col_2
0      3     a
1      2     b
2      1     c
3      0     d

data.value: DataFrame from dict of array-like or dicts.
